subSubSection.paragraph:
Acizzia keithi
sp. n.
can be distinguished from all other species of
Acizzia
by the following suite of characters: antenna short, 1.0–1.2 times width of head (
Fig. 11
); genal processes short, 0.23– 32 times length of vertex, with broad, blunt apices (
Fig. 11
); both sexes with characteristically mottled wings (
Figs 12–16
); male proctiger with thin, erect apical node and broadly-triangular lateral (posterior) lobes without terminal distal appendages (
Fig. 17
); apical segment of aedeagus thin, with little-expanded apex (
Fig. 17
); hind margin of parameres with inconspicuous basal node (
Fig. 17
); inner face of parameres with short rod-shaped setae in a medial field, and a short blunt, triangular node at basal third (
Fig. 18
); female terminalia long, proctiger and subgenital plate elongate triangular from lateral aspect (
Fig. 19
).
